<item>
            <title>[PIG-3120] setStoreFuncUDFContextSignature called with null signature</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3120</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m currently working on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3015&quot; title=&quot;Rewrite of AvroStorage&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-3015&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-3015&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and am having trouble passing the UDFContextSignature to the store func. It looks like the store func on the head end is being set to a non-null value, but a null value is being passed to setStoreFuncUDFContextSignature on the back end. I&apos;m opening this ticket to track this issue; I&apos;ll follow up with a reproducible test case when I have a clean one.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I suspect this problem occurs when running on a real cluster, but may not occur in the standard unit tests.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
